    <main>
        <h1>LeetCode 1784: Check if Binary String Has at Most One Segment of Ones (C++)</h1>

        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                Given a binary string s without leading zeros, return true if s contains at most one contiguous segment of ones. Otherwise, return false.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: s = "1001"<br/>
                Output: false<br/>
                Explanation: The ones do not form a contiguous segment.<br/><br/>
                Input: s = "110"<br/>
                Output: true<br/>
                Explanation: The ones form one contiguous segment.<br/><br/>
                Input: s = "1"<br/>
                Output: true<br/>
                Explanation: There is only one segment of ones.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    bool checkOnesSegment(string s) {
        // Check if "01" exists in the string
        // If it does, it means there's a zero followed by a one,
        // which indicates more than one segment of ones
        return s.find("01") == string::npos;
    }
};</code></pre>
